tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE quantum_experiments (
  experiment_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_date DATE,
  experiment_type TEXT,
  outcome_result TEXT,
  measurement_value FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE quantum_experiments (
  experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_name TEXT NOT NULL,
  quantum_system TEXT,
  measurement_outcome TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE experiment_results (
  result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_id INT NOT NULL,
  measurement_time TIMESTAMP,
  measurement_result FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE quantum_systems (
  system_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  system_name TEXT NOT NULL,
  qubits INT,
  gates_used TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE measurement_devices (
  device_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  device_name TEXT NOT NULL,
  manufacturer TEXT,
  quantum_compatible BOOLEAN
)

CREATE TABLE quantum_experiments (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_name VARCHAR(255),
  start_time TIMESTAMP,
  end_time TIMESTAMP,
  outcome TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE experimental_conditions (
  condition_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_id INT,
  temperature FLOAT,
  pressure FLOAT,
  humidity FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE measurement_data (
  data_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_id INT,
  measurement_time TIMESTAMP,
  measurement_result FLOAT,
  measurement_error FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE experimentalists (
  experimenter_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(255),
  email VARCHAR(255),
  affiliation VARCHAR(255),
  experience_years INT
)

CREATE TABLE equipment (
  equipment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  equipment_name VARCHAR(255),
  manufacturer VARCHAR(255),
  purchase_date DATE,
  warranty_period INT
)
